and more effective. The Worker Center Handbook compiles best practices from around the country on partnering with labor, enlisting the assistance of faith communities and lawyers, raising funds, developing a serious membership program, integrating civic engagement work, and running major campaigns. The authors urge center leaders to both organize and build strong administrative systems. Full of concrete examples from worker centers around the country, the handbook is practical and honest about challenges and opportunities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunity centerszUnited StatesvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aCommunity centerszUnited States. 0aLabor movementzUnited StatesvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aLabor movementzUnited States. 0aLabor unionsxOrganizingzUnited StatesvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aLabor unionsxOrganizingzUnited States. 4aLabor History. 4aReference.  aWorker centers, labor, community, organizations, campaign, raise funds.1 aCasillas Pabellon, Marien, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2016z9783110485332oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170589240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501705892423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501705892/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-DSWb2016